3.1.2 Data Structure
--------------------

Arrays are represented as balanced tree structures of the form `Array
T', thus `Array' may be used as a type tag to restrict variables in
pattern matching.

  The internal data structure `T' is a binary tree built with the
following constructors:

 -- constructor: array::nil
     the empty tree.

 -- constructor: array::tip value
     a leaf of the tree, holding the given value.

 -- constructor: array::bin balance left right
     a nonempty tree with the given balance flag (0 or 1) and left and
     right subtrees.

  (This is for informational purposes only. The tree constructors are
private, and client modules must not rely on the internal
representation.)


